---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import PhotoMarquee from '../../components/PhotoMarquee.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';

const photos = [
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-1.jpg', alt: 'Shockwave therapy session' },
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-2.jpg', alt: 'Shockwave treatment' },
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-3.jpg', alt: 'Shockwave application' },
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-4.jpg', alt: 'Shockwave therapy' },
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-5.jpg', alt: 'Shockwave treatment in progress' },
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-6.jpg', alt: 'Targeted shockwave treatment' },
	{ src: '/shockwave-therapy/sw-slider-7.jpg', alt: 'Shockwave assessment at Balance' },
];

const bookingUrl = 'https://go.mindbodyonline.com/book/widgets/appointments/view/8068777f5e/services';

const faqs = [
	{ q: 'Is shockwave therapy painful?', a: 'It can be uncomfortable, but the intensity is adjusted to remain tolerable.' },
	{ q: 'How many sessions will I need?', a: 'Most people benefit from a short course of 3–5 sessions.' },
	{ q: 'Are there any side effects?', a: 'Mild soreness, redness, or bruising can occur temporarily after treatment.' },
	{ q: 'Can I exercise afterwards?', a: 'We usually recommend reducing heavy loading for 48 hours, then progressing as advised.' },
	{ q: 'How is this different from an injection?', a: 'Shockwave is a pro-inflammatory modality, whereas an injection is usually a steroid-based injection which is anti-inflammatory.' },
	{ q: 'Do I need a referral?', a: 'Yes, unless you are seeing (or would like to see) Steve our podiatrist, as he can confirm diagnosis with ultrasound that there is no tendon tear. Shockwave would make a tendon tear worse.' },
];
---
<Layout
	title="Shockwave Therapy in Clapham"
	description="Shockwave therapy in Clapham for persistent tendon and soft tissue conditions, integrated into a structured rehabilitation plan at Balance Performance Physiotherapy."
>
	<PageHero title="in Clapham" highlight="Shockwave Therapy" breadcrumb="Shockwave Therapy" />

	<PhotoMarquee images={photos} heightPx={140} speedSeconds={45} />

	<div class="service-intro">
	<ImageText eyebrow="Our approach" heading="When pain lingers, it usually means" highlight="something hasn't fully healed" image="/shockwave-therapy/body-1.jpg" imageAlt="Shockwave therapy in progress">
		<p>Shockwave therapy is designed for exactly that: persistent tendon and soft tissue problems that haven't responded to rest, exercise, or standard treatment.</p>
		<p>At Balance, we use shockwave as part of a wider, structured rehabilitation plan. The goal isn't just to reduce pain, but to restart the healing process and so you can move forward.</p>
		<p><a href={bookingUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">Book Now</a></p>
	</ImageText>
	</div>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="The treatment" heading="What is" highlight="shockwave therapy?" image="/shockwave-therapy/body-2.jpg" imageAlt="Shockwave equipment close-up">
		<p>Shockwave therapy uses controlled acoustic pulses delivered directly into the affected tissue.</p>
		<p>This stimulates a response in the body that helps:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Improve blood flow to the area</li>
			<li>Reduce pain sensitivity</li>
			<li>Encourage tissue repair</li>
		</ul>
		<p>It's a non-invasive treatment that can be particularly effective when progress has stalled.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText eyebrow="Symptoms" heading="When shockwave" highlight="can help" image="/shockwave-therapy/body-3.jpg" imageAlt="Shockwave treatment for tendon pain">
		<p>Shockwave therapy is commonly used for chronic tendon conditions, including:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Plantar fasciitis (heel pain, especially first steps in the morning)</li>
			<li>Achilles tendinopathy</li>
			<li>Patellar tendon pain (below the knee)</li>
			<li>Tennis or golfer's elbow</li>
			<li>Shoulder tendon pain or calcification</li>
			<li>Lateral hip pain (greater trochanteric pain)</li>
		</ul>
		<p>If you've tried other approaches without lasting improvement, this may be the next step.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Treatment" heading="How we" highlight="use it" image="/shockwave-therapy/how-we-use-treatment.jpg" imageAlt="Shockwave treatment being applied to a foot at Balance Physio">
		<p>Shockwave isn't a standalone fix.</p>
		<p>We integrate it into our broader rehabilitation plan, combining it with the right loading, movement work, and progression back to activity.</p>
		<p>Treatment is targeted and controlled. Each session typically lasts around 20 minutes, and the intensity can be adjusted to suit you.</p>
		<p>The aim is to create the right conditions for healing, not just mask symptoms.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText eyebrow="Outcomes" heading="How we measure" highlight="your progress" image="/shockwave-therapy/body-5.jpg" imageAlt="Tracking shockwave therapy outcomes">
		<p>We track more than pain levels.</p>
		<p>We look at how your tendon tolerates load, how your movement improves, and what you're able to return to over time.</p>
		<p>This allows us to:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Progress your rehab safely</li>
			<li>Reduce the risk of recurrence</li>
			<li>Build long-term resilience in the tissue</li>
		</ul>
		<p>You'll have a clear sense of where you are, and what's improving.</p>
		<p><a href="/outcomes" class="section-link">Read More About Outcome Measures &rarr;</a></p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Our patients" heading="Who we" highlight="help" image="/shockwave-therapy/who-we-help-treatment.jpg" imageAlt="Shockwave treatment being applied to a calf">
		<p>Shockwave therapy is particularly useful for:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Runners and athletes with persistent tendon injuries</li>
			<li>People dealing with long-standing heel or elbow pain</li>
			<li>Individuals who haven't responded to previous treatment</li>
			<li>Those looking to avoid injections or surgery where possible</li>
		</ul>
		<p>It's often the turning point when recovery has plateaued.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText eyebrow="What to expect" heading="During your" highlight="session" image="/shockwave-therapy/screen-shot-2019.webp" imageAlt="Shockwave session">
		<p>Treatment involves applying a handheld device that delivers shocks to the affected area.</p>
		<p>You may feel a deep, rhythmic tapping sensation during the session. This can be uncomfortable at times, but is generally well tolerated and can be adjusted as needed.</p>
		<p>Most people require a short course of treatment, typically spaced over a few weeks.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Fees" heading="Pricing and" highlight="insurance" image="/shockwave-therapy/body-last.jpg" imageAlt="Shockwave at Balance">
		<p>We offer a transparent fee structure that reflects our level of clinical expertise. We're also recognised by all major insurance providers, including Bupa and AXA Health.</p>
		<p><a href="/pricing#additional-physio" class="section-link">Pricing Information &rarr;</a></p>
	</ImageText>

	<section class="faq-section faq-section--alt">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="section-header"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2></div>
			<div class="faq-list">
				{faqs.map((item) => (
					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary>{item.q}</summary>
						<div class="answer">{item.a}</div>
					</details>
				))}
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
